                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12055: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-14T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 14, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>244. From Murphy.<note n="23" xml:id="d322fn23">Robert D. Murphy, Counselor of
                        Embassy in France, temporarily at Algiers, with responsibility for
                        supervision of the North African economic aid program.</note> I learn from
                    an excellent source that a group of 20 German Armistice delegates arrived here
                    yesterday to take possession of military automotive equipment stored in Algeria
                    since the Armistice. This equipment, the exact amount of which I do not know,
                    was requisitioned shortly after the Armistice and delivery thereof is in
                    accordance with the terms of the Convention. However, my informant states that
                    when the equipment arrives in Libya it will prove worthless because great pains
                    have been taken to so doctor mechanical parts that even a slick used car dealer
                    would be impressed.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Vichy. [Murphy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
